<br>
<br>
now i havent had a large amount of time to compare the two, but my initial *feal* is that the obsidian does a mutch better job at obtaining aggro,, where the bbb's rune proc needs the mob already aggro on you too realy instigate good hate..<br>
<br>
  say if u were trying to get a mobs attention, and your bbb was proc'n  it wouldnt do as mutch as the obsiadian taunting blow proc to turn the mob onto you,, but after the mob was on you the rune proc is very effective,, <br>
<br>
the bbb has a lower proc rate it *seems*  . its comprable to say a primal 2h,, streaky,,  im intristed to find out if sews has a higher proc rate than the bbb, the rune proc though does produce some intence aggro,, now the obsidian greatblade has a high proc rate i *feal*,, the effect is taunting blow, it goes off alot,, but theres no mistake,n the BoW has far more aggro than either,, ,, normaly clearing content i would get a mob turned on me ,off of the ma from time to time.  but if she/he are wielding a Bow the mob sticks on em like glue. without a doubt the best war 2hand aggro producing  weapon..<br>
well it hasnt been a long time with them both ,, but from the hip this is what i have experianced between the OGB and the BBB <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=minet>minet</A> at: 4/7/03 12:49:48 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bburlydorf>BBurlydorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/03 5:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: aggression</span><hr size=1> A number of people have asked questions or given opinions about weapons that might belong on the lower part of the list. I thought I'd contribute my impressions.<br>
<br>
Windblade, TSBS, etc. are not aggro weapons. Since these do not have a proc, the only aggro they generate is based on DPS. Warriors are not the top melee damage dealers, so you can count on other melees with higher DPS &quot;stealing&quot; aggro from you if you use these.<br>
<br>
Weapons that have pure DD or DoT effects without stun or knockback are not aggro weapons. Neither are weapons that give you life or buff you.<br>
<br>
Aggro weapons proc an increase in hate (TB/EB), slow, stun, knockback, and a very very few other aggro producing effects.<br>
<br>
The major reason that some weapons with these procs do not appear on this list is that their proc is resistable. For this reason, the Cord Hilted Spike Driver is IMO the best easily obtained lower level aggro weapon - it's proc is unresistable.<br>
<br>
Other lower-end aggro weapons are useful when their proc isn't resisted. These include Blade of Strategy, Jagged Blade of War, Willsapper, Trident of the Deep Sea, the Troll smithed Yaks, Wavecrasher, Frostbringer, Ichorflow, etc. For this reason, I'd advise not weilding 2 aggro weapons with the same resist - mobs are seldom resistant to both Fire and Cold for example.<br>
<br>
Until you can obtain weapons on the upper end of this list, these lower-end aggro weapons are perfectly servicable in most pre-PoP raids/groups and infinately superior to a Windblade.<br>
<br>
BB <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=1ludor>1Ludor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 175<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/03 7:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: aggression</span><hr size=1> resist doesnt have much to do with it. i use norg most the time and after MT goes down, hes coming for me hehe.<br>
<br>
resists on slow, stun, and knockback all produce great agro. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=577575&amp;resize=true" target="top">Ludor Sheolbane</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
