</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bburlydorf>BBurlydorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/10/03 4:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: aggression</span><hr size=1> True - Slow, stun, and knockback produce aggro even when resisted. But, given a choice I'd use my Guadralek instead of your Norge'tal - against highly or 100% magic resistant mobs Guadrelek will outperform it in aggro and in DPS.<br>
<br>
Even if the DPS was the same, Cord Hilted Spike Driver is superior to Blade of Strategy.<br>
<br>
In raid situations with other melees procing slow, stun, knockback, root, etc. the MT should be a little concerned if their stuff is sticking and his is not - Earthcaller, Petrified Hearwood Flambarge, etc. are used in raids and as the MT you need to out-aggro them.<br>
<br>
With 4 aggro weapons to chose from, I use the ones that aren't being resisted. With unresistable procs, you don't even have to watch for resist messages to see if you want to change weapons.<br>
<br>
BB<br>
